TextAnnotation.Text: Contra In dyatessaron Linquendo primam pausam
Altus supra cantum precedam vos in galileam In dyatessaron
Altus. Canon. precedam vos in galileam in subdiatessaron.
Altus in diatesaron liquando primam pausam
Altus supra cantum precedam vos in galileam Indyatesaron

Rest.EditorialCommentary: This extra passage, copied at the beginning of the staff (top of a new opening) corresponds to the "et expecto" motive at m. 169; one can surmise that this was copied accidentally onto this opening from an exemplar in which the section was split across two openings, with the extra notes at the beginning of the second opening as a cue/reminder for the canonic voice.

Note.EditorialCommentary: Over erasure in MS; originally G?
